Chickpea Vegan Meatloaf

2x14oz cans or 3 1/3 c cook chickpeas, drained and rinsed
1 onion, diced
2 celery stalks, chopped
2 carrots, diced
2 garlic cloves, minced
2 c panko bread crumbs
1/2 c unflavored soy or almond milk
3 tbsp vegan worcestershire sauce
2 tbsp shoyu or tamari
2 tbsp olve oil
2 tbsp ground flax seeds
2 tbsp tomato paste
1 tsp liquid smoke
1/4 tsp black pepper

Preheat oven to 375F. Lightly oil a 9" loaf pan. Working in batches if needed, place all meatloaf ingredients into food processor and pulse until chickpeas are broken up and ingredients are well mixed. Stopping to scrape down the sides as needed. Do not overblend. If working in batches, transfer each batch to a large mixing bowl when complete and mix by hand. Press mixture into a prepared loaf pan and bake for 30 min. 

Glaze:
1/4 c tomato paste
2 tbsp maple syrup
2 tbsp apple cider vinegar
1 tbsp shoyu or tamari
1 tsp paprika

Combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Remove loaf from oven after 30 min and spoon glaze over the top. Bake another 20-25 min. Remove from oven and allow to cool at least 10 min before cutting.
